The `XBR Market <https://github.com/crossbario/xbr-protocol/blob/master/contracts/XBRMarket.sol>`__

params.account: The account to grant maintainer rights to.

params.coin: The ERC20 coin to be used as the means of payment in the market.
params.consumerSecurity: The amount of coins a XBR consumer joining the market must deposit.
params.maker: The address of the XBR market maker that will run this market. The delegate of the market owner.
params.marketFee: The fee taken by the market (beneficiary is the market owner). The fee is a percentage of                  the revenue of the XBR Provider that receives coins paid for transactions.                  The fee must be between 0% (inclusive) and 100% (inclusive), and is expressed as                  a fraction of the total supply of coins in the ERC20 token specified for the market.
params.marketId: The ID of the market to create. Must be unique (not yet existing).
params.providerSecurity: The amount of coins a XBR provider joining the market must deposit.
params.terms: Multihash for market terms set by the market owner.

params.created: Block number when the market was created.

The fee must be between 0% (inclusive) and 100% (inclusive), and is expressed as                  a fraction of the total supply of coins in the ERC20 token specified for the market.
params.marketId: The ID of the market to create. Must be unique (not yet existing).
params.member: The member that creates the market (will become market owner).
params.providerSecurity: The amount of coins a XBR provider joining the market must deposit.
params.signature: EIP712 signature created by the member.
params.terms: Multihash for market terms set by the market owner.

params.delegate: The delegate to get the current paying channel address for.
params.marketId: The XBR Market to get the current paying channel address for.

params.actorType: The type of actor under which to join: PROVIDER or CONSUMER.
params.marketId: The ID of the XBR data market to join.
params.meta: The XBR market provider/consumer metadata. IPFS Multihash pointing to a JSON file with metadata.

params.actorType: The type of actor under which to join: PROVIDER or CONSUMER.
params.joined: Block number when the member joined the market.
params.marketId: The ID of the XBR data market to join.
params.member: The member that creates the market (will become market owner).
params.meta: The XBR market provider/consumer metadata. IPFS Multihash pointing to a JSON file with metadata.
params.signature: EIP712 signature created by the member.

params.apiCatalog: The ID of the API or API catalog to which the consent shall apply.
params.delegate: The address of the off-chain provider or consumer delegate, which is a piece                 of software acting on behalf and under consent of the actor in the market.
params.delegateType: The type of off-chain delegate, a data provider or data consumer.
params.marketId: The ID of the XBR data market in which to provide or consume data. Any                 terms attached to the market or the API apply.
params.servicePrefix: The WAMP URI prefix to be used by the delegate in the data plane realm.

params.apiCatalog: The ID of the API or API catalog to which the consent shall apply.

params.marketId: The ID of the XBR data market in which to provide or consume data. Any                 terms attached to the market or the API apply.
params.member: Address of member (which must be actor in the market) that sets consent.
params.servicePrefix: The WAMP URI prefix to be used by the delegate in the data plane realm.
params.signature: EIP712 signature, signed by the consent setting member.
params.updated: Block number at which the consent setting member has created the signature.

addMaintainer(address).notice: Add a new maintainer to the list of maintainers.

countMarkets().notice: Get the total number of markets defined.

countMarketsByOwner(address).notice: Get the number of market owned by the specified member.

createMarket(bytes16,address,string,stri.notice: Create a new XBR market. The sender of the transaction must be XBR network member and automatically becomes owner of the new market.

createMarketFor(address,uint256,bytes16,.notice: Create a new XBR market for a member. The member must be XBR network member, must have signed the transaction data, and will become owner of the new market.     /// Note: This version uses pre-signed data where the actual blockchain transaction is submitted by a gateway paying the respective gas (in ETH) for the blockchain transaction.

currentPayingChannelByDelegate(bytes16,a.notice: Lookup the current paying channel to use for the given delegate in the given market.

currentPaymentChannelByDelegate(bytes16,.notice: Lookup the current payment channel to use for the given delegate in the given market.

getAllMarketConsumers(bytes16).notice: Lookup all consumer actors in a XBR Market.

getAllMarketProviders(bytes16).notice: Lookup all provider actors in a XBR Market.

getAllPayingChannels(bytes16,address).notice: Lookup all paying channels for an provider actor in a XBR Market.

getAllPaymentChannels(bytes16,address).notice: Lookup all payment channels for an consumer actor in a XBR Market.

getMarketActor(bytes16,address,uint8).notice: Get market actor data for the given actor (address) and actor type in the specified market.

getMarketMaker(bytes16).notice: Get the market maker for the given market.

getMarketOwner(bytes16).notice: Get the market owner for the given market.

getMarketsByOwner(address,uint256).notice: Get the n-th market owned by the given member.

isActor(bytes16,address,uint8).notice: Check if the specified member is actor in the given market.

isMaintainer(address).notice: Check if the given address is currently a maintainer.

joinMarket(bytes16,uint8,string).notice: Join the given XBR market as the specified type of actor, which must be PROVIDER or CONSUMER.

joinMarketFor(address,uint256,bytes16,ui.notice: Join the specified member to the given XBR market as the specified type of actor, which must be PROVIDER or CONSUMER.     /// Note: This version uses pre-signed data where the actual blockchain transaction is submitted by a gateway paying the respective gas (in ETH) for the blockchain transaction.

setConsent(bytes16,address,uint8,bytes16.notice: Track consent of an actor in a market to allow the specified seller or buyer delegate to provide or consume data under the respective API catalog in the given market.

setConsentFor(address,uint256,bytes16,ad.notice: Track consent of an actor in a market to allow the specified seller or buyer delegate to provide or consume data under the respective API catalog in the given market.     /// IMPORTANT: This version uses pre-signed data where the actual blockchain transaction is submitted by a gateway paying the respective gas (in ETH) for the blockchain transaction.
